{
  "texts": [
    "However, this is often not the case.",
    "A recent survey of the ML literature indicates that mitigation efforts are overwhelmingly focused on the modeling stage, even though problems and biases are often identified and measured at earlier stages of problem formulation and data collection and processing [16].",
    "There is no \"one size fits all\" data bias mitigation strategy.",
    "The effectiveness of data bias mitigation strategies would depend on the sources of bias and on the application [6].",
    "For example, in the presence of representation bias, data augmentation through the collection of additional data samples of underrepresented groups could be an effective bias mitigation strategy."
  ]
}